Such a neighborhood gem!! So many great things I have to say about this place. Hawaiian Hideout offers a variety of drinks and delicious Asian fusion food options, all at a very reasonable price. The drinks are generally between $8-10 and the dishes are generally $10-15. We found our drinks to be STRONG and refreshing, and our pad see ewe and panang curry to be delicious. The food portions seemed a bit small, but honestly with the prices of the drinks, we didn't feel too bad about it. There's also a vegan section of the menu and lots of options for people with dietary restrictions, which I was impressed by.  In addition to food, service was friendly and reasonable. But the most impressive part of the restaurant has got to be the beautiful, authentic decor that transports you to the beach in Hawaii. Can't wait to bring our friends back here!
Food was amazingly delicious and staff was so sweet! Drinks were also fabulous! Will definitely be returning for more great food and memories

Lovely place, and quick service.  Food: I was surprised by the amount vegan options that were on the menu, I tried 3 of these: the Ramen, the lumpias, and the veganese rice. All of these were enjoyable( I recommend tthe lumpias, even though they were just an entree, they tasted great), the one thing I couldn’t eat was the ramen that I ordered, the ramen was HUGE, so maybe if I haven’t ordered the other things I could’ve eaten half of the ramen...  Ambient: the decoration is mostly Hawaiian and the music is Hawaiian too, there are some Japanese type art objects around the place too.  Location: I walked from cloud gate to the restaurant, the neighborhood was safe, the restaurant was easy to get to.  Service: they have a good costumer service, very patient too.  Visited on 10/17/20
If you love Hawaii and Polynesia but can't get there from here...this is your spot!

We are continually impressed with the quality of food from Asian Outpost.  We have been ordering delivery regularly since the pandemic and the food comes well packaged and quick (We order directly from the AO not through a delivery app). As a vegetarian, I love how many options I have (they have an entire Vegan/GF menu but will also modify non Vegan meals if you want).  Their Panang is probably some of the best I've had, and we had it in Thailand! If you eat at the restaurant you must get the Panang sweet potato fries. Seriously the most delicious bite ever! I usually get the panang with veggies and tofu for take out because it's saves better.  Their Vegan Lumpia's are so tasty, we get two orders because we'll fight over them if we don't! They also have a good selection of veggie sushi, my husband (non veggie) loves their Sunomono roll and says they do a really nice job on Nigiri as well.  The in person dining was always fun, but with the exception of a couple patio meals, we haven't been able to experience it this year.  Overall, well developed flavors, nice portions, great service, why wouldn't you support this local gem??? Thank you AO for being a staple in our neighborhood.

This is the strangest “Asian restaurant” I’ve ever been to in Chicago. My first time here I ordered ramen. It was noodles in soup, alright, but tasted nothing like ramen. The soup was light, not at all like the tonkatsu it’s advertised to be. Noodles were somewhat hard and bland, and overall was just a very mediocre dish that doesn’t taste like ramen at all. After that ramen experience I thought, “pho is pretty simple, surely they can’t screw that up too, right?” I just had pho here and it was NOT pho. The broth is dark, not like clear broths I’ve had at other pho places. The beef pieces were different as well,  not the steak and flank I was expecting. It was beef, but an unusual cut. The broth was way too spicy because the jalapeños were already in the soup, instead of being set aside on another plate like other places usually do. I mean, this certainly LOOK like an Asian restaurant, but it just strikes me as a place that’s forgotten how to be Asian. If you’re looking for a more “authentic” or traditional experience, avoid this spot. I was hungry and made the same mistake twice, but I won’t again.

Let me start with the positives, their staff is great friendly, competent, and efficient; usually pretty low key, quiet; decent patio (though I always get the feeling you are so far from the staff that they might forget you).  Once upon a time we loved their chicken, not sure if the chef changed or was out, but this last time it was dry and they forgot to send out with it's special sauce; the nasi, though tasty, was heavy on the rice (almost like a bi bim bop, just cheaper veggies); and the lettuce wraps, again tasty, but so much sauce (growing up a friend's mom used to make these with the sauce as a dip, so I might be a little biased here).  As for the drinks my wife's knocked her on her butt after 4 sips (colada) but she says it tasted good, mine the Dr was way too syrupy (my guess the dash of caracao turned into finger or more) almost like cough medicine (or my early drinking years), they were however very quick to take that and bring me a beer (my suggestion to use less caracao was met with the suggestion the bartender may still make very similar, fair).  To be fair, I only ever liked their chicken so I came in not expecting much, and got less than that.  My overall would be a pass, but their menu is large enough, that by the law of averages there has to be better options, I just have not found them yet.

great cocktails and amazing food! I highly recommend the Vietnamese Pho and the veggie pad Thai :)

Ugh, ordered pho. I was served minced noodles and broth w beef and 2 jalapeños,  no sprouts, onions, basil, cilantro etc. noodles were basically mush. Called to complain and was told, "well, what do you want me to do about it..." very unprofessional and rude.
Good service, food and environment!
Great Asian food.  We sat Al Fresco.  Service was prompt.  Good was tasty.  Poke bowl, sushi... All good.
Good food.
I only had diarrhea for 2 days.  Highly recommend
Sushi is very good, but ramen is bad.....

We visited with a child with a peanut allergy in our group who wanted to sample everything, but only realized it when the food arrived at the table. Our server Natty was so wonderful and accommodating, patiently and kindly running back to the kitchen to check on everything we asked about to make sure it was safe. Then, one dish took longer than the others, and she brought that person extra soup and snacks while they waited. Top notch service in addition to excellent food!
Food was fantastic!
Awesome food and service

This place is so fantastic and they are featuring a new Vegan and Gluten Free menu! I had the Vegan Hot & Sour Tofu Veggie Soup. It was extremely flavorful, and opened up all my sinuses! lol I definitely will come back and try all the other 🌱 friendly entrees!

I love Asian Outpost! This place has a fantastic menu of many Asian meals. The garlic fried chicken is a must. We also had great maki, and the Raman selection is great. The Indonesian spicy seafood, is great if you like spicy.
Great sushi with lots of variety.
Great place. Food is plentiful. Prices are reasonable. Service is awesome.

It's been a while since Ive been here but I'm dying to go back!! I tried the ramen and something else I think egg rolls?? I can't remember but I just remember I loved the food and atmosphere. Very relaxing 😎 for a date on Sunday... I'll be back soon...

I have been eating at Asian Outpost for a few years now with more than two dozen orders. Sometimes I eat in and sometimes I make a pickup order. The place is a little different and I suppose that is what keeps me going back. The food has always been very good. The chicken and pork belly sliders are a couple of my favorites. They made some menu adjustments a few months ago and enjoy some of the new dishes like the Panang Chicken.  It has a relaxed and friendly atmosphere with a neighborhood vibe to it. Asian Outpost serves some great asian comfort food and is a great asset to the neighborhood.

Over rated! We ate there shortly after they opened at 5 PM. We must have gotten reheated leftovers from the night before. Pad Thai was over cooked. Shrimp was overcooked. Sushi was ok.  Staff was nice. Sake was lukewarm.
Good food, excellent service, very pleasant atmosphere.
Good food and great service. The server was very attentive and put up with our large group including 5 children very well.
The food is really good but the service needs some improvement.

This place was awesome! The food and drinks were so good and super affordable. There are plenty of vegan/vegetarian options to choose from. The service was great. The ambiance was very relaxing. We still can't believe how cheap it was to dine here! Definitely recommend when you're in Chicago!
Great food. The ribs and fried chicken were so good
Food is not traditional, and not what expected, but nice atmosphere. Service is a little slow most evenings I've been there. I live close by so sometimes it's just convenient
Wonderful food and service. Mongolian Deluxe was devine.
There is a much-expanded menu than when it first opened, and is now one of the best restaurants in the South Loop. They have many options and do them all well. The sushi is phenomenal.
Great ambiance, wonderful food, and courteous servers. The location is also within walking distance from downtown.
Great pork belly sliders and best Ramen I've had!

This was definitely good. The price is a little up there if I remember correctly. They get points for location too. Haha. Yes they get all of us from the center because we all love Asian food. It's a good mix and selection and I'll have to try more dishes from here. Some things I saw coming to other tables made me wish I had ordered that because it looks delicious! My noodles were good too.

Hubby and  I  ate dinner for $31, including 2 soft drinks.  Prices are reasonable.   Food is great.  Had Mom's garlicky fried chicken.   THE BEST CHICKEN EVERY.  Also, basil chicken  and it was really good.
Was in search of something different for supper.  Walked around for a bit and came across this restaurant.  Very friendly people, nice atmosphere, and AWESOME food.  Highly recommended.

Love this south loop restaurant. We stumbled across it on a walk around the neighborhood and absolutely loved it. The food is fantastic and reasonable for sushi and for wine.  They have black rice sushi which I highly recommend! They service is always great, no complaints here!
Nice restaurant with good food (their green curry is good!) and service.
Lunch portions a bit small. Menu descriptions a bit off. But, tasty and affordable.

We recently moved to the South Loop and this was the first restaurant we decided to explore. It was so good. For dinner I had the Ginger Chicken, which by the way, YUM! For an appetizer we had Calamari and an amazing dip to go with it! It was so good that we asked the waiter how they made it. The prices were decent for a Chicago restaurant. For two people including a drink, a shared appetizer and two entrees, we had a total of $35. I would definitely go here again for dinner and bring my visitors here.

Best tasty food for Ramen, Ribs, Steak, and Sushi!!! Variety of fantastic drinks, especially the hot Sake!!! Great prices, service, and food! The best is the Pork Belly Sliders, Ribs, and Ginger Garlic Fried Chicken!!! Best prices and awesome food! Also, you can eat on the patio! Great assortment of drinks!
Really good garlic chicken. Like really really good.
Good ambience. Great food!
Great atmosphere.  Waiting staff was very courteous and friendly, and even the simple sushi rolls were presented nicely on the plate!

Had a great experience. Our table ordered a few different things starting with drinks and appetizers. The drink with the green tea syrup was really good and the wonton chips and dip was great too. For entrees we got a variety of sushi and also the fried chicken. The best sushi was the one made with black rice, I highly recommend it. Also, the fried chicken with the miso butter corn bread was amazing. It was perfectly crisp and amazingly juicy. There was nothing bad about it. It is probably the best fried chicken I have ever had. The service was also very good. Very helpful and knowledgeable about the menu. If you're thinking about trying this restaurant do!  You won't regret it.

Went there with a groupon, and had one of those rare "I would actually pay full price for this" moments.  I sampled a lot of the menu. It's mostly small plates meant to be shared, but the entrees are reasonably sized and could feed one not-so-hungry person. The menu is truly Asian fusion, but there is something for everyone to like - BBQ pork belly to sushi. The food was very well prepared and very tasty.  Further, they have outdoor seating and some daily drink specials (I went on Wed. for 1/2 price Sapporos) which, combined with small plates and lots of finger food, makes this a great place to get snacks and drinks in the summer.  The service was also very good, but they weren't particularly busy so that's kind of to be expected.  All-in-all, the experience is very fairly priced. I won't wait around for another groupon before going back.
Had the ribs and chicken. The flavor was good. The ambiance was nice and relaxing. They play slower cover versions of pop songs (kind of weird at first) .
Great Vietnamese sandwiches. Terrific service.

After reading some great reviews about Asian Outpost, I decided to check it out and see what the hype was all about. Everyone was raving about their fried chicken, so I decided to give it a try. Amazing. Seriously juicy fried chicken.  Apparently they put it in a pressure fryer to keep it so juicy. The chicken comes with a sweet & tangy Asian-flavored sauce that takes the flavor to another level. The fried rice and the soup that I had were good, but not as good as the chicken - that is definitely their signature dish.  The service was really good, and the ambiance was interesting. I felt like I was in a quirky antique furniture store and there were all kinds of things to look at on the walls and ceiling. I would suggest Asian Outpost for a casual, neighborhood dinner with friends. Support the South Loop and check it out!
Food and service is fine, nothing noteworthy. I don't understand all the fried chicken comments, doesn't seem very special.
